\sin^2(x)+\cos^2(x)=1
 \begin{align*} \sin^2(x)-\cos^2(x)&=\sin^2(x)+\bigl(\cos^2(x)-\cos^2(x)\bigr)-\cos^2(x)\\ &= (\sin^2(x)+\cos^2(x))-2\cos^2(x)\\ &= 1-2\cos^2(x). \end{align*} 
